    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-08-28T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-08-28T13:00:00-05:00" n="538"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d538">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751.5 <gloss target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss>/8–2852:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 538<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France (<persName corresp="#p_ACHILLESTC1"
                            type="from">Achilles</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-08-28T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 28, 1952—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1274. <gloss target="#t_Cotel1">Cotel</gloss>. Joint Emb <gloss target="#t_MSA1"
                        >MSA</gloss> Mission <gloss target="#t_MSG1">msg</gloss>.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Had very useful informal discussion at lunch today given by <persName
                            corresp="#p_DRAPERWHJ1">Draper</persName> for <persName
                            corresp="#p_PLEVENR1">Pleven</persName>. Others present were <persName
                            corresp="#p_ALPHANDH1">Alphand</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_ACHILLESTC1">Achilles</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_MERCHANTLT1">Merchant</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_LABOUISSEHRJ1">Labouisse</persName>.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PLEVENR1">Pleven</persName> outlined difficulties he
                        had had in developing French 52 mil budget in light many demands on French
                        overall budget, such as Indochina operations, reconstruction of severe
                        damages of last war, and need for all mil production in France. Pointed out
                        is having serious problem developing 53 budget and emphasized important
                        relationship to this work of US plans for <gloss target="#t_OSP1"
                            >OSP</gloss>.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>He stressed importance of knowing as soon as possible range of items we
                        are prepared to purchase as well as those we will definitely rule out. Only
                        in this way can he build realistic mil budget and mil program. He also
                        expressed disappointment that nothing tangible had been done to follow up on
                        procurement MD–452 and ammo which we had stated a willingness to procure
                        (subj of course to caveats as expressed on our ltr to <persName
                            corresp="#p_PLEVENR1">Pleven</persName> of July 12—see <gloss
                            target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 303 July 12<note n="1"
                            xml:id="d538fn1">
                            <ref target="#d526">Document 526</ref>.</note>).</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>During course of mtg, we pointed out to <persName corresp="#p_PLEVENR1"
                            >Pleven</persName> various difficulties which confronted us in this
                        field, but stated wld endeavor move quickly. We earnestly hope that
                        everything possible will be done in Wash to expedite action in this regard.
                        Specifically, we urge fol: <list>
                            <label>(a)</label>
                            <item>Technical team be dispatched promptly to review situation with
                                respect to MD–452 aircraft. Believe this team shld include man with
                                broad experience in aviation industry. (<persName
                                    corresp="#p_PLEVENR1">Pleven</persName> said wld welcome such
                                team and anything US cld do to assist rapid substitution of Mark IV
                                for Mark II).</item>
                            <pb facs="0151" n="1241" xml:id="pg_1241"/>
                            <label>(b)</label>
                            <item>Expedite procurement ammo by appropriate instructions to
                                procurement officers. (<persName corresp="#p_PLEVENR1"
                                    >Pleven</persName> mentioned great need for production land
                                mines, and hope this can be considered.)</item>
                            <label>(c)</label>
                            <item>Expedite action on spare parts procurement. (In this connection,
                                we are informed by French that French Ford Co and others ready and
                                willing bid.)</item>
                            <label>(d)</label>
                            <item>Expedite action in determining needs in electronics field and in
                                starting procurement.</item>
                            <label>(e)</label>
                            <item>Prompt decision on points raised in <gloss target="#t_Tomus1"
                                    >Tomus</gloss> 101<note n="2" xml:id="d538fn2">See <ref
                                        target="#d535fn6">footnote 6, Document 535</ref>.</note> and
                                    <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 941.<note n="3"
                                    xml:id="d538fn3">Summarized in the memorandum by <persName
                                        corresp="#p_BYINGTONHMJ1">Byington</persName>, <ref
                                        target="#d537">
                                        <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>
                                    </ref>.</note>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>During meeting, we pointed out unfortunate repercussions which flowed from
                        recent publicity over <gloss target="#t_OSP1">OSP</gloss>. <persName
                            corresp="#p_PLEVENR1">Pleven</persName> seems to have been particularly
                        nettled by A 1 friendly art in <hi rend="italic">Wash Post</hi>, and
                        attributed largely to that art his statements to press. He has calmed down
                        and gives impression of desire to work out problems in amicable manner. If
                        we can move forward on matters mentioned para 4 above, believe will do much
                        to restore relations and to facilitate achievement many of our common and
                        natl objectives.</item>
                    <label>6.</label>
                    <item>Separate tel covers <persName corresp="#p_PLEVENR1">Pleven</persName>’s
                        views re airbase agmt.<note n="4" xml:id="d538fn4">This is a reference to
                            telegram 1266 from Paris, Aug. 28. (711.56351/8–2852) Documentation
                            concerning the negotiations over the airbase agreement with France is in
                            file 711.56351.</note>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ACHILLESTC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Achilles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
